docker run -d -p 3000:3000 --name Abathur -v /home/docker/:/root -e FLASK_APP=app.py -w /root python:2-slim bash -c "apt update && apt upgrade -y && pip install flask && flask run -h 0.0.0.0 -p 3000"

Wait for the docker to finish installing the pacages then run:
``` sh
docker cp app.py Abathur:/root
```

app.py:

from flask import Flask

app = Flask(__name__)
@app.route('/')
def msg():
    return '<h1>Hello World</h1>'
